President Obama announced his intent to nominate Peggy Goldwater Clay as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Barry Goldwater Scholarship and Excellence in Education Foundation. Clay is currently the Chair of the foundation and has experience in various roles, including being a board member and former president of Goldwater's Foods of Arizona, a Community Relations consultant, and the owner and President of Peggy Jane's Inc., a salad dressing company. She has also served in leadership positions in organizations such as the University of California, Irvine Foundation and the Air Force Academy Foundation. Clay has received recognition for her contributions, including being named the Distinguished Woman of the Year by the Orange County Soroptomists and Woman of Valor by the American Diabetes Association of Orange County. She is the youngest daughter of former Senator Barry Goldwater.